 History\". BrooklynNets.com. NBA Media Ventures, LLC. Archived from the original on November 15, 2019. Retrieved November 19, 2019.^ \"Nets will be all-Brooklyn by 2015-16: Team unveils $50M Industry City training center\". New York Daily News. June 26, 2014. Archived from the original on August 8, 2014. Retrieved July 31, 2014.^ a b \"Pro Basketball \u2013 Nets' New Practice Facility Befits a First-Class Team\". The New York Times. February 18, 1998. Archived from the original on August 11, 2014. Retrieved July 31, 2014.^ \"Damage moves Nets practices\". New York Post. November 1, 2012. Archived from the original on June 30, 2015. Retrieved July 31, 2014.^ Coon, Larry. \"NBA Salary Cap FAQ \u2013 2011 Collective Bargaining Agreement\". Archived from the original on May 27, 2015. Retrieved April 13, 2014. If the player is already under contract to, or signs a contract with a non-NBA team, the team retains the player's draft rights for one year after the player's obligation to the non-NBA team ends. Essentially, the clock stops as long as the player plays pro ball outside the NBA.^ \"Brooklyn Nets Complete Three-Team Trade with Phoenix and Memphis\". NBA.com. February 8, 2024. Retrieved February 8, 2024.^ \"Kings Complete Trade With Brooklyn Nets\". NBA.com. February 8, 2023. Archived from the original on February 8, 2023. Retrieved February 8, 2023.^ \"Brooklyn Nets acquire future draft considerations in five team trade\". NBA.com. August 6, 2021. Archived from the original on August 7, 2021. Retrieved August 6, 2021.^ \"Suns acquire Kevin Durant from Nets in blockbuster trade\". February 10, 2023. Archived from the original on June 19, 2023. Retrieved June 4, 2023.^ a b \"Brooklyn Nets Complete Three-Team Trade\". BrooklynNets.com. July 6, 2019. Archived from the original on July 6, 2019. Retrieved July 6, 2019.^ a b \"Nets: Players\". Basketball Reference. Archived from the original on April 1, 2023. Retrieved April 10, 2023.^ \"Brooklyn Nets Uniform Numbers\". B