 .202 hitter Michael Jordan was a better MLB prospect than, say, Tim Tebow\". Archived December 9, 2020, at the Wayback Machine. Los Angeles Times. Retrieved October 30, 2023.^ \"1994 Birmingham Barons\". Baseball-Reference.com. Archived from the original on July 4, 2021. Retrieved October 30, 2023.^ \"Michael Jordan Statue\". United Center. June 2013. Archived from the original on April 3, 2017. Retrieved October 30, 2023.^ Artner, Alan G. (November 2, 1994). \"Jordan Truly Larger Than Life: Sculpture Shows Spirit Of The Man, But Little More\". Chicago Tribune. Archived from the original on October 6, 2012. Retrieved April 27, 2022.^ \"Bye-bye, No. 23: Buzz went to see Michael Jordan's Chicago...\" Chicago Tribune. November 8, 1994. Archived from the original on August 12, 2012. Retrieved April 27, 2022.^ \"1993\u201394 Chicago Bulls Roster and Stats\". Basketball Reference. Archived from the original on September 14, 2008. Retrieved October 22, 2022.^ Taylor, Phil (March 20, 1995). \"What Goes Up ... Must Come Down, Or So It Seems\". Archived April 30, 2018, at the Wayback Machine. Sports Illustrated. Retrieved October 30, 2023.^ Lazenby, pp. 513\u2013515.^ Lazenby, pp. 511\u2013512.^ Collier, Jamal (May 10, 2020). \"'I'm back.' Everything you need to know about Michael Jordan's 1995 return to the Chicago Bulls\u2014and the famous 2-word fax that preceded it\". Archived March 23, 2021, at the Wayback Machine. Chicago Tribune. Retrieved October 30, 2023.^ a b \"Michael Jordan returns to Bulls in overtime loss to Indiana Pacers \u2013 Chicago Bulls\". Jet. Vol.\u00a087, no.\u00a021. Johnson Publishing Company. April 3, 1995. pp.\u00a051\u201353. ISSN\u00a00021-5996. Retrieved April 7, 2022 \u2013 via Google Books.^ Hausman, Jerry A.; Leonard, Gregory K. (1997). \"Superstars in the National Basketball Association: Economic Value and Policy\". Journal of Labor Economics. 15 (4): 586\u2013624 [587]. doi:10.1086/209839.^ \"1994\u201395 Chicago Bulls Schedule and Results